fields.title: ARBIS
fields.html_footer: Partners:
fields.html_info:
ARBIS - Assam River Basin Information System
ARBIS incorporates various sources of geodata (in situ / satellite) concerning river dynamics of the Brahmaputra river. The goal is, to provide a powerful webbased geoinformation portal to support scientists and local authorities in Assam / India. ARBIS was developed by codematix GmbH and the Friedrich-Schiller-University, both from Jena / Germany. Contact: Carsten Busch codematix GmbH Felsbachstraße 5 / 7 07745 Jena cbusch@codematix.de 0049 3641 3038-0 (phone) 0049 3631 3038-20 (fax)

The data was created from OpenStreetMap map data (www.openstreetmap.org). OpenStreetMap (OSM) is a collaborative project to create a free editable map of the world. (Licence before 12.9.2012: CC-BY-SA 2.0).

fields.abstract: Land use derived from LANDSAT satellite data acquired 2010-01-06 and 2010-01-30 by object oriented image classification.
fields.title: Land use Assam and Meghalaya, 2010

fields.abstract: River gauging stations in Assam, India at which one or all of the following parameters are monitored: Water level,G, in meter above sea level (m asl), discharge, D, in cubic meter per second (cbm/s), sediment concentration, SC, in grams per liter (g/l). The latter is referred to the monitored discharge to calculate load, SL, in tons per day (t/d). Stations monitoring all of the three parameters are named GDS-stations. Daily time steps are recoded but water level readings are carried out three times a day (08:00; 12:00 and 16:00) from which the daily mean is calculated.
fields.title: Gauging Stations

fields.abstract: Layer showing the braiding dynamics of the Brahmaputra River flow channels derived from the classification of Landsat images by means of object orientated image analysis. Landsat images corresponding to the respective dates of the time slider bar are provided in the layer 'Landsat Images'.
fields.title: Braiding Dynamics

fields.abstract: River training measures in Assam, India, comprise all engineering infrastructures applied in the Brahmaputra River to protect against bank erosion, flooding and to support river channelization.
fields.title: River Training Measures

fields.abstract: Landsat Images of Assam. Channels displayed: 3 (red), 2 (green), 1 (blue).
fields.title: Landsat Images

fields.abstract:
Layer showing the likelyhood of river channel location derived from analyzing the braiding dynamics of the Brahamputra River channel network. Altogether thirteen datasets covering a time period from 1989 until 2014 were used for the likelyhood analysis. Likelyhood of channel development is given in percent of datasets analyzed and indicates the tendency of the channel system to be static.

Example: A value of 0 % at a particular location in the braided river bed means that in all data sets analysed no flow channel was found and in turn a value of 100 % means that a flow channel was classified in all data sets.
fields.title: Channel Development
